<title type="html"><![CDATA[Uhh... the NES CPU clock]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1675&amp;p=14340#p14340"><![CDATA[
So really, the NES has a variable average frame rate from 60.098814 to 60.0991250 frames per second. The first is the most common and the second fairly rare (Battletoads, my 410-color demo). You could get intermediate rates by enabling PPU rendering late only on certain frames.  Perhaps somewhat useful, with the help of a <a href="http://www.math2.org/math/general/arithmetic/fradec.htm" class="postlink">page of fractions that yield repeating decimals</a> I found that 1789772.7272... = 1789772 + 8/11.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Wed Jun 21, 2006 12:23 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
