<div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />- 341 PPU cycles per line;<br /></div><br />Yep. Except for the first line on every other frame, which is 340.<br /><div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />- 262 lines;<br /></div><br />Yep. See above.<br /><br />Using the above two numbers, the average number of CPU cycles per frame is 29780.5.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />- 60 frames per second.<br /></div><br />Nope. To get the framerate, divide the CPU speed (1789772.7272727... Hz) by that number.<br /><br />The result: ~60.098814 frames per second.<br /><br />How? NTSC sets are reasonably tolerant of the video signal you send them, as long as it's within spec - while the spec technically calls for exactly 59.94Hz (for color TV), 60.0988Hz is within 0.3% of that and is technically still valid.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Wed Jun 21, 2006 10:45 am</p><hr />
